      "date": "2024-09-11 04:35:39.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2:\n> \n> Unless there is a reason not to do so, it would probably make sense to update this directly from the kernel list.h...\n\nYou want current list.h to be updated with newer include/linux/list.h?  The one which is more atomic proof with READ_ONCE() etc... + plus some more macros defined. Pease let me know if I got your instructions correct.",
